# Compass environment configuration.
# Copy this file to .env and uncomment / fill in values as needed.

# --- Anthropic authentication ----------------------------------------------
# Compass authenticates only through the Claude Code OAuth credentials
# file at `~/.claude/.credentials.json`. Setup:
#
#   1. Install Claude Code (https://claude.com/download or
#      `npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code`).
#   2. Run `claude /login` once. The CLI writes the OAuth tokens.
#
# That's it — Compass reads the file directly and bills against your
# Claude.ai subscription quota (no API-credit usage). API keys are NOT
# used; we don't even read ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.

# --- SEC EDGAR identification ----------------------------------------------
# SEC requires every EDGAR request to identify the caller. Both values are
# required when running `compass fetch <TICKER> <FORM>`. Use a real name and
# a contact email so SEC can reach you if your traffic causes issues.
# See: https://www.sec.gov/os/accessing-edgar-data
#
# COMPASS_SEC_USER_NAME=Your Name or Company
# COMPASS_SEC_USER_EMAIL=you@example.com

# --- Optional overrides ----------------------------------------------------
# COMPASS_DEFAULT_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
